radiographic_examinations.findings: Moderate amount of ascites, nodular liver, small right pleural effusion, bibasilar subsegmental atelectasis, tiny hiatal hernia, dense material in the stomach indicating possible previous oral contrast, gallbladder distended with dense material, no focal mass in liver, extensive atherosclerotic calcification of the aorta, no retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy, no pneumoperitoneum, no free gas in pelvis, sigmoid diverticulosis.
